snippet.textDisplay:
I do not think that the Viral Video Age is quite over. I do believe the golden age of viral videos are over though. These newer ones will not be as iconic or have as long of a shelf life as they did in the Chocolate Rain days.

But I will argue that more will see it quicker. Even as a flash in the pan sensation. Just there is more people online these days. Which sadly means it is easy to burn out a meme these days. Also things get viral in the vast different niches in the web these days. So though not unanimously known as the days of yore. They are still pretty well known in their own right.
